<p class="Normal" xmlns:news="http://www.dotnetnuke.com/modules/news" xmlns:newsext="urn:NewsExtensions">Employers are ramping up their use of social media screening and real-time employee monitoring in 2019. And the demand for workers in a tight labor market will push more companies to consider applicants they may have once ignored: those with criminal records.<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/shrm/hrnews/~4/noO2Ul6LyWs" height="1" width="1" alt=""/></p>
